First Overview¶

Text(0, 0.5, 'Performance')

Multivariate Anomaly Detection with Isolation Forest Method¶

Text(0.5, 1.0, 'Contamination = 0.05')

  • Isolation Forest model has been created with a contamination value 0.05

  • Anomaly score has been given to the values (between (-1,1))

  • As a result, it can bee sen that, when xkurt sensor get more than 5, it creates anomaly.
